// Kodex API Routes
// REST API endpoint router for the Kodex knowledge management system.
// Dispatches to handler functions for topics, flags, drafts, dashboard,
// and missing-topics based on path and HTTP method. Requires a project
// query parameter on every request.

FUNCTION handleKodexAPI(req) -> Response                                   EXPORT
  CALLS: getKodexManager (kodex-manager)
  Require the "project" query parameter; return 400 if missing.
  Obtain a kodex manager instance for the project.
  Route the request by path suffix and HTTP method:
    GET  /topics              -> handleListTopics
    GET  /topics/:name        -> handleGetTopic
    POST /topics              -> handleCreateTopic
    PUT  /topics/:name        -> handleUpdateTopic
    DELETE /topics/:name      -> handleDeleteTopic
    POST /topics/:name/verify -> handleVerifyTopic
    POST /topics/:name/flag   -> handleFlagTopic
    GET  /flags               -> handleListFlags
    PUT  /flags/:id           -> handleUpdateFlag
    GET  /drafts              -> handleListDrafts
    POST /drafts/:name/approve -> handleApproveDraft
    POST /drafts/:name/reject  -> handleRejectDraft
    GET  /dashboard           -> handleDashboard
    GET  /missing             -> handleMissingTopics
  Return 404 for unmatched routes.
  Return 500 with the error message on unexpected exceptions.

---

FUNCTION handleListTopics(kodex, includeContent) -> Response
  List all topics via kodex.listTopics().
  IF includeContent is false, return the metadata list directly.
  IF includeContent is true, fetch full content for each topic in parallel
  and return the enriched list.

---

FUNCTION handleGetTopic(kodex, name) -> Response
  Fetch the topic by name with full content. Return 404 if not found.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateTopic(kodex, req) -> Response
  Parse request body for name, title, content, and optional createdBy.
  Return 400 if any required field is missing.
  Create the topic as a draft via kodex.createTopic. Return 201 with the draft.

---

FUNCTION handleUpdateTopic(kodex, name, req) -> Response
  Parse request body for content (partial) and reason.
  Return 400 if either is missing.
  Update the topic via kodex.updateTopic and return the resulting draft.

---

FUNCTION handleDeleteTopic(kodex, name) -> Response
  Delete the topic via kodex.deleteTopic. Return 204.

---

FUNCTION handleVerifyTopic(kodex, name, req) -> Response
  Parse verifiedBy from body. Return 400 if missing.
  Verify the topic, then fetch and return the updated topic (metadata only).

---

FUNCTION handleFlagTopic(kodex, name, req) -> Response
  Parse type and description from body. Return 400 if either is missing.
  Create a flag via kodex.createFlag. Return 201 with the flag.

---

FUNCTION handleListFlags(kodex, status) -> Response
  List flags, optionally filtered by status. Return the list.

---

FUNCTION handleUpdateFlag(kodex, id, req) -> Response
  Parse status from body. Return 400 if missing.
  Update the flag status via kodex.updateFlagStatus. Return the id and new status.

---

FUNCTION handleListDrafts(kodex) -> Response
  Return all pending drafts.

---

FUNCTION handleApproveDraft(kodex, name) -> Response
  Approve the named draft via kodex.approveDraft. Return the resulting topic.

---

FUNCTION handleRejectDraft(kodex, name) -> Response
  Reject the named draft via kodex.rejectDraft. Return a success message.

---

FUNCTION handleDashboard(kodex) -> Response
  Return dashboard stats from kodex.getDashboardStats.

---

FUNCTION handleMissingTopics(kodex) -> Response
  Return the list of missing topics from kodex.getMissingTopics.

---

FUNCTION jsonError(message, status) -> Response
  Wrap a message string in { error } and return it with the given HTTP status.
